	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Greetings!  <BR>
<BR>
I would share a few tidbits of info as well.  I have a few bard characters, one is the main one in mid-20's.  I have been playing for a long time though since I am not much of a powerleveler.<BR>
1)The jig does not add to mana regen.  It DOES appear to because of the updates to the health/mana/stamina bar.  Eventhough the Hymn updates only the health bar, the jig does all of them.  In other words, jig &quot;heals&quot; stamina, but updates all the changes to your bars more often, while the Hymn &quot;heals&quot; health, but doesn't update the changes to all the bars.  I don't know of a better way to put this so if it is unclear I am sorry.<BR>
<BR>
2)Avoid the mino axe.  Try to get a dragoon dirk as soon as possible.  Almost everyone touts the mino axe.  It SEEMS attractive, but bards miss often and it is a stamina drain.  A fine steel weapon is the way to go until you can afford to buy a dragoon dirk.<BR>
<BR>
3)The level 2 song, Dissonance is amazing!  When the pvp team servers went up I started a bard on one.  At level 2 I bought this song to try to &quot;pull&quot; some mobs.  There were over 200 people around Kelethin trying to kill stuff.  My first few bards shied away from the song because I feared fighting more than one beastie at a time.  Just the one seemed tough enough.  But this song on the pvp team server was amazing!  I was killing wasps, wolves, orc pawns, and more at 3-4 a time.  I was clothed in patch work armour and wielding a tarnished long sword (a rusty long sword that has been polished).  I was gaining a level about every 1 1/2 to 2 hours up to level 5.  I was amazed!<BR>
<BR>
4)Do the mail run quests when moving from place to place.  Bards need money badly to pay for songs, armour, weapons, etc.  Running back and forth from Kelethin to Freeport and collecting at the stops on the way can make a person several gold peices with very low risk.  If you are going anyway, always deliver the mail!<BR>
<BR>
5)One other way to raise quick cash in Kelethin is to do the &quot;drum&quot; quest over and over again, selling the drums!  This is what i used to do before the mail quest was up.  Don't know if they still allow you to do the quest more than once now though.<BR>
<BR>
6)Group often!  Especially with clerics.  Bards are public enemy number one it seems.  If you are in Qeynos be very wary of the Karanas!!  Lions have been seen breaking off from fights to go and hassle a bard!<BR>
<BR>
7)Beware of area effect songs in dungeons and in places like Unrest!<BR>
<BR>
There is more, but I have spoken enough.  Enjoy playing the best class in the game.  Try doing different things.  It is easy to fall into a rut. The bard class is so diverse it is difficult to discern that there is a better approach than the one you are using.  One example:  two level 22 bards in the Karanas soloing.  One is killing gorge hounds one at a time by melee and bellow, then using Hymn to restore lost hitpoints.  Other bard is also fighting one gorge hound at a time by melee and using Dissonance,Discord, and Hymn at the same time by twisting.  Bard two kills faster, has no down time for healing, and kills 4 gorge hounds in the time bard one kills one hound and heals up.  And here is the kicker!  Another bard comes along soloing 4 hounds at once!  But i noted his down time was fairly long while he healed up.  The point is to try different tactics to see what works in a particular situation.<BR>
<BR>
Above all have fun!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
