			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hello there, I'm rather new to the EQ world, I just started playing 2 weeks agow.. I am a Bard of the 13th song and think I might have a tip that could help alot of you<BR>
<BR>
Forgive me if this has been posted befor<BR>
<BR>
ok..<BR>
<BR>
While messing with the socials I found out that you can do commands in them.. after a bit of research I came to a way to be singing 4 songs at ones with not even as much effort as singing 2<BR>
<BR>
creat a new social.. name it what ever you want.. I name mine 1-2, 3-4, 5-6, and 7-8<BR>
<BR>
then add these lines<BR>
<BR>
/pause 27,/cast 1<BR>
/pause 5,/cast 1<BR>
/pause 27/cast 2<BR>
/pause 5/cast 2<BR>
<BR>
by doing this it will cast the first song you have mem then as soon as it take effect it stops it and casts what you have in mem slot 2<BR>
just change the numbers for other slots<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
BTW if anyone can figure out how to tweek this more let me know!
				</font>
			</td>

