			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				After reviewing information on all races, and classes, I decided on a Halfelf Bard. In the begining things went well. I met felow lowbies, we kiled &quot;yard junk&quot; and lvled together. However after about lvl 9, I noticed I was less effective, and more vulnurable than my counter part druids, Rangers, etc. I then became aware of the &quot;twisting of song&quot; technique, that allowed me to off-set my lack of HP, and AC, that my buddies had. It worked! But now at 19 I once again am suffering from a lack of stats that inhibit me from progreessing independent of a group, or in some cases contributing sufficiently to the group.  <BR>
<BR>
That was until the other nite. I often susspected that my heal song had some benefit, but while the casters in my group were &quot;meddin&quot;, to regain mana, I took a note of their health. We had just come off a frenzied battle in Omin, and everyone was mid to low on health. During the pause my heal song was on. By the time the casters were ready for a pull, everyones health was 75 pluss %.<BR>
<BR>
There is nowhere else you are going to get those results without having a caster down during battle. I wish evryone was aware of the benifits of the bard. BUT, be prepared to be poor. Bards can only assist while in group, (except for corpse find, and thats newbie stuff, they have no cash.) You can't sell a SOW, or BIND, or PORT.  But, u can provide help, ( all be it unnoiticed help,) that can keep your party alive.<BR>
<BR>
Yes I know I didn't mention the other songs that can be of tremendious value, but this thing is too damn long already.<BR>
<BR>
Copart<BR>
Bard of the 19th song<BR>
Clan Destine<BR>
Bertoxxulous server
				</font>
			</td>

