				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I dunno who said not to buy Chords of Dissonance... but this is a MUST have.  I'm lvl15 now, and if I'm in a group where I need to help melee, I will still almost always twist this song in.  This is what'll offset your leeser melee damage compared to a pally/warrior.  Even with bellow now, I really only use that kiting while soloing.  Frankly, if you're in a group, bards usually need to be meleeing at lower lvls... if you just sit back many groups won't think you're doing a thing... and chords lets them NOTE your importance, esp if you can anthem and heal them at the same time.<BR>
At lower levels, who cares if big powerful NPCs kill ya while you're singing it? Why are you singing an attack spell in a town, anyway?!  Your mistake--not a flaw in the song. You don't see newbie wizzies casting shock of frost at guards do you?  Of course not.<BR>
Anyway, long story short--my most useful song up to lvl15 besides selo's. Gives even non-belivers in bards some good proof of their usefulness.
